Program: Omnibus
Title: Aunt Ida's Hospital
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376ldh
Last Broadcast Date: 20 December 1996
Dr Ida S. Scudder became a doctor when she discovered women in India could only be treated by female doctors. This programme tells her story and looks at the work of the internationally renowned hospital she founded in Vellore, India.